    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>LEAD: The police detained a Jewish settler in the occupied West Bank after he accidentally shot and wounded two Israeli soldiers while chasing a Palestinian who hurled a firebomb at his car, officials said today.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>LEAD: The police detained a Jewish settler in the occupied West Bank after he accidentally shot and wounded two Israeli soldiers while chasing a Palestinian who hurled a firebomb at his car, officials said today.</p>
        <p>The police detained a Jewish settler in the occupied West Bank after he accidentally shot and wounded two Israeli soldiers while chasing a Palestinian who hurled a firebomb at his car, officials said today.</p>
        <p>''He thought they were terrorists coming to kill him,'' said David Bedein, a spokesman for Jewish settlements in the area.</p>
        <p>In the shooting, on Wednesday, Gedalia Becker accidently shot the soldiers near the Jewish settlement of Efrat, about 10 miles south of Jerusalem, as he chased the Palestinian, an army official said. The soldiers were not seriously hurt. Mr. Becker, a resident of the Maalei Amos settlement, was released after questioning.</p>
      </block>
